{
  "title": "A Good Place for Swimming",
  "transcript": "I'm going to talk about a good place for swimming, which is located in the back of our village. There are a lot of places where you can go swimming, especially if you live near a rural area. Some people go to the beach, but I don't live near the seaside. So I go swimming in the, uh, it's like a lake but it's man-made. In many ways, I think swimming is the healthiest sport people can do. You can train every part of the body by swimming. Well, summer is the best season for swimming because the water is warm. And then you need to make sure you have all your swimming gear, like a towel, swimming glasses. I think they're called a goggle, no no, goggles. Also, you need a bag to keep everything in. You should probably take some water to drink, as the water in the river isn't safe for drinking. Oh, and maybe some food because you might get hungry if you're out all day. I usually go in the afternoons because the water tends to be warmer once the sun has been shining on it most of the day. Swimming is quite simple once you learn how to do it, just move your arms and legs in rhythm. I love it because I feel so relaxed afterwards. It's dangerous to swim here if you aren't careful. I usually avoid swimming near the waterfalls, and more specifically places where water goes over the edge of waterfalls. All in all, swimming is a wonderful activity. It's a great way to spend a summer afternoon.",
